reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful design, super compact, but the wind it produces is too weak
reviews.reviewText: I really like how this handheld fan looks. It's also great how compact and lightweight it is.For those that don't like vibration, this fan is really solid and has pretty low vibration. So you can hold it for long periods of time without your hands getting uncomfortable.However, the wind it produces is just too weak. The lower fan speeds just don't work well enough outside when you're walking around. You have to bring the fan really close to your face to really feel it. Basically, you have to use a higher fan speed for it to be effective. With a higher fan speed, it gets noisier too.Additionally, the wind it produces is very narrow, likely due to how small it is and the enclosed design it uses. So you need to aim it carefully.I also got the larger version of this and I feel like this smaller one is better overall.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on July 21, 2022
reviews.reviewText: After reading multiple reviews about how quiet and powerful this is I purchased two. There’s no other way to put it apart from these fans are very underwhelming in terms of the power, even on max they need to be held pretty close to your face to feel anything. I know it’s a small fan with a small blade but I expected better. They’re also quite loud as well. For the amount of sound coming from it (I certainly wouldn’t use it on public transport due to the noise) you expect a lot more. All things aside it’s not a bad fan, it does the job, it looks pretty slick, it’s lightweight, easy to carry around however if I was in the market again for another handheld fan I’d probably look elsewhere.
